{
  "texts": [
    "Portfolio optimizationWhile the analytical results of Section 4 only apply to MaxCut and QAOA with transversefield mixer B = j x j, the intuition applies more broadly.",
    "To illustrate this point, in this Section we consider a portfolio optimization problem with a budget constraint, given bymin x∈{0,1} N qx T Σx -µ T x,(89)s.t.j x j = k. (90)This problem is commonly considered as a target for QAOA [52,11,53,54,55,56].",
    "We use random instances generated by RandomDataProvider in qiskit finance [57] and set q = 0.5 and k = ⌊ n 2 ⌋.",
    "We consider 20 for each number of qubits between 7 and 20, for a total of 280 instances.",
    "For each instance, we reformulate the problem in terms of spin variables and rescale the objective following Equation (8), with the scaling coefficient computed separately for each instance."
  ]
}